---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Consent and Compliance in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for consent and compliance by permission handling, preference centers, suppression, pricing context, sources, and practical tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Teams managing detailed consent and preference states','Profiles, forms, segments, and conditional flows','Requires careful legal and data governance','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail teams coordinating email and SMS consent','Accessible campaign and multichannel workflows','Regional rules and channel opt-outs need QA','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean stores with straightforward email permissions','Focused sequence operations','Validate compliance tooling and audit exports','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Marketing and transactional messages across regions','Broad messaging and contact options','Streams and permissions need separation','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small stores starting with basic consented email','Native customer and campaign setup','Limited advanced preference governance','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Consent is not a checkbox added after the campaign is written. The store needs a clear purpose, source, permission record, preference path, suppression behavior, and process for honoring changes.</p><p>We compare operational fit, not legal guarantees. Review applicable laws and vendor terms with qualified counsel, and verify current pricing and permission features from official sources before launch.</p><h2>Shortlist for consent-aware stores</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First governance project</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Preference and suppression map':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Email/SMS permission QA':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Source-aware welcome':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Marketing/transactional split':'Native opt-in review'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for consent and compliance</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when the store can document purpose, source, permission, retention, and suppression for each audience. Platform settings support compliance operations but do not determine the merchant’s legal obligations.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with one signup source and audit the entire path—from form language to unsubscribe and suppression. Measure complaint rate, opt-outs, data-quality exceptions, and support issues; do not present compliance as a guaranteed platform outcome.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a governed lifecycle test; can use Shopify signals.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; legal review and merchant process remain necessary.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans for contacts, forms, sends, seats, SMS, and audit features.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Governance priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Detailed preference states</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible profiles and suppression logic.</td></tr><tr><td>Simple email permission path</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused operations are easier to audit.</td></tr><tr><td>Native early-stage opt-in</td><td>Shopify Email</td><td>Low-friction starting point.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/consent-compliance">consent-compliance guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
